which means that students are not concentrating when they are supposed to .
As a result , it can affect their lives and studies .
This then could lead to stress as these students are not able to cope with their studies because they were distracted in class .
In my opinion , every individual has to take responsibility for their own lives by making the right decisions .
There are advantages and disadvantages in using social media sites , however , in this case , striking a balance between social media and their real lives is the most important thing to do .
Nowadays , the use of social media platforms is commonplace in our lives .
In an increasingly globalised world , such platforms enhance and complicate the links between people .
Thanks to these platforms , people can get to know one another online without having to travel to meet up for business purposes or personal reasons .
However , it also brings some social changes whereby such virtual worlds are overtaking the real world , negatively impacting people 's daily lives and therefore becoming a larger problem for societies as a whole .
As people spend more and more time on social media sites , the importance of face-to-face human contact has decreased .
As people feel more confident and comfortable online where they do not have to face real-life , on-the-spot situations , they prefer communicating online .
This results in a lack of interpersonal skills , especially in young students , as they always have the option to turn their backs to the real world and go online .
This becomes a huge problem when they have no choice but to face things in real life .
As they are so used to having an online avatar , they may lose their self-identity in their real life and not understand how to interact with people face-to-face .
Another problem with social media is that the consequence of investing such an enormous amount of time and energy is not reflected as something positive to the users .
The reason why it is so addictive is that the more people get into social media , the more attention they seek from their friends .
However , such sparks of sudden attention are extremely short-lived and disappear quickly , and thus do not add any value or meaning to the users lives .
Also , according to a research study , users feel sadder after using Facebook , which is because users unknowingly compare their lives with other people 's lives .
But seriously , most people only post the happiest moments in their lives .
Social media definitely has a strong benefit that make users stay , which is how it links people together .
Indeed , I myself use Facebook just because of the friends that I want to keep in contact with .
However , friendship in a virtual world is so superficial that it is not so relevant to the real world .
Also , as numerous profit-driven companies realize the huge amount of traffic on such social media sites , they treat it like a pond to fish in for customers by uploading a lot of advertisements .
Furthermore , this also possibly triggers privacy issues because Facebook allows some profit-driven companies to access the users ' information .
As this happens , users are more and more prone to possible frauds .
Social media sites are at their peak at the moment , however I believe that when people realize that such sites are not making them better people in real life , they will not indulge in them as much as they do now .
Soon users will realise that they do not need social media sites to keep in touch with their friends because , if they really need somebody , they will reach their friends no matter what .
We think we are all connected through all types of social media , but are we really being connected or falling apart ?
Social media sites like Facebook and Twitter were created with the intention of connecting people from around the world .
The idea was great , and nowadays most people , even the older generation , have an account on at least one social media platform like Facebook .
Parents are now " friends " with their kids and they can " follow " their kids more closely and in real time .
People post their random thoughts or daily activities via Twitter and they frequently post different kinds of photos on Facebook to connect with their so-called friends .
However , we then tend to spend too much time on social media , resulting in a significant reduction of face-to-face human contact , which eventually affects our interpersonal skills .
First and foremost , I would like to share the advantages of using social media in my daily life .
As a student , I tend to meet lots of people from different backgrounds in different settings .
We may meet only once but we exchange our phone numbers and Facebook accounts in order to keep in touch .
Unlike just having phone numbers that we may not even call , social media sites like Facebook are a great way for friends from different fields or even different parts of the world to stay connected .
With a few clicks , we can check on a friend 's profile and read their status updates .
We can also update our profiles by making wall posts , which our friends can read on their newsfeeds .
This allows friends that may not have the time to meet in person to still be connected in a way .
Not only that , but new friends can also be easily met through such online platforms .
As a result of this , our social circle is indeed expanding .
Nonetheless , what seems to make us connected can also be what causes us to fall apart .
The obvious disadvantage of using social media is the reduced time spent on face-to-face contact .
This subsequently leads to poor interpersonal skills that inhibit the growth of our real social circles .
For example , we tend to send birthday wishes when Facebook prompts us , " Today is someone 's birthday " , when in fact , we may have forgotten our friend 's birthday .
when in fact , we may have forgotten our friend 's birthday .
We used to send greeting cards for festivities like the Chinese New Year , and it felt so good to write one and of course to receive one with stamps on it .
Gone are those times , and now we send mass e-mails and the receivers may feel less meaning in these online wishes .
As time passes , we may have more " friends " on our contact list , but the meaning of the word " friend " needs to be redefined .
In a nutshell , social media is a double-edged sword .
The users of all social media sites need to strike a balance between the real world versus the virtual one .
We should maximize the benefits of such platforms but be careful of their impacts on our actual lives .
Ultimately , the best way to enhance interpersonal skills is still through face-to-face meetings , and social media sites are just tools to supplement it .
Social media sites are commonly used in today 's society .
I believe that 80 percent of people use social media sites .
These sites play the role of connecting people around the world .
They serve the function of connecting people , sharing content , interacting with others and advertising .
However , there are some disadvantages to social media that concern the society .
This article is written to explain the pros and cons of using social media in our daily lives .
First , with social media sites that connect people , anyone can interact and communicate with their friends , families , and even strangers without any time or place constraints .
Through social media sites , we can chat with our friends who are visiting Europe or New Zealand .
There are over one thousand miles between Singapore and these two countries , but we are still able to chat with our friends without traveling there .
but we are still able to chat with our friends without traveling there .
This saves a lot of money and time , as well as strengthens our relationships even though we are in different places around the world .
Besides that , companies can also use the convenience of social media sites , such as Facebook chat or Skype , to facilitate business meetings with people from around the world .
Substantial cost is saved without tiring travel from one point to another .
The huge amount of cost savings can be utilized in other sectors , which could benefit the company more and boost the company 's profit .
However , there are always two sides to a story .
Some scholars argue that the use of social media reduces the personal connections between people .
Since ancient times , humans have interacted with each other face to face .
Without facial expressions , it is easy to misunderstand a person 's intent .
That is why facial expressions are one of the most important elements in social learning .
In addition , a popular point of view in society is that " social media sites will affect writing skills " .
Based on a research report , writing skills are reduced more when more time is spent on social media sites .
I believe most of us have had the experience of suddenly forgetting how to write a word that we should have known .
Auto-correct software is so effective when using electronic devices that we do not realize the importance of writing .
Writing is an essential skill for people to express their feelings and opinions .
Privacy ' has been a popular word in the past few decades .
Each person has their own rights and privacy .
I believe that most of us agree with these statements .
However , there has been news about social media sites leaking users ' information to companies for cash reimbursement .
Everything we type in social media sites is recorded on their servers and then transferred to companies for spying and advertising .
Even though it appears that there are no rules and it is your own space to speak and do anything you want , you are actually wrong .
You are not only controlled by the government 's laws but also spied on by the government .
In conclusion , there are two sides to every story .
It is our responsibility to identify the advantages and disadvantages of social media sites .
To utilize this technology well , we should do our best to not only balance the pros and cons but also lengthen the list of pros and shorten the number of cons .
In this way , social media can bring a prosperous future to us and to the next generation .
With the widespread use of advanced technology , social media sites are becoming more and more popular .
Getting connected on social media sites , such as Facebook and Twitter , has become a popular trend as well as part of our daily work .
In this situation , both the advantages and disadvantages of using social media apply to our daily lives .
On one side , it has brought many obvious advantages to our lives .
Social media provides people with the opportunity to contact each other , any time and anywhere .
Whether we are at home or at school , at work or on a holiday , we can communicate and interact with our friends .
Even when people are thousands of miles apart , social media makes it possible to interact with each other by writing messages .
When our phones are accidentally out of battery , we can use social media to get in touch with our friends .
Some people who are too shy to talk in public can actively take part in group chats via social media .
Besides , we can make more friends through these interactions when our friends bring their other friends in .
Therefore , the popularity of social media sites has made it more convenient for people to update their friends and contact them more frequently .
On the other side , we need to consider the negative influences of social media .
There are many disadvantages of using social media .
First , interpersonal skills may be affected by the reduction in face-to-face human contact .
While social media brings convenience to people 's lives , people are more and more willing to use social media for chatting instead of talking in person , which has a time and place requirement .
People who are not good at speaking with others may be more reluctant to talk to people , and their interpersonal skills can never be improved in this situation .
Second of all , a social media addiction may exacerbate social alienation to some degree , and this kind of alienation causes some social media users to suffer from over-dependence on virtual networking .
More and more networking has been transferred to the internet from real life .
This is one potential danger for teenagers , who are going through social development .
Third , a lot of posts are about luxurious living standards as well as other ways of showing off may make people 's daily lives seem more and more grandiloquent , which is not an accurate portrayal .
Finally , it is easy for people to waste a lot of time using social media .
Again , there is a trend for them to suffer from social media addiction , which may greatly harm their education and work .
We can see both the advantages and disadvantages of using social media , but since we can not deny the huge benefits that it has brought to us , it will likely be around for a long time .
Therefore , every time we use social media , we should take both sides into consideration and try to avoid being affected by the disadvantages .
Only by absorbing the essence and discarding the dregs can we make better use of social media .
In a sophisticated era like today , experts keep producing inventions that are meant to make life easier .
Geographic borders are not a problem anymore because communication and information technologies are continuously being enhanced .
The telephone was likely perceived as the biggest innovation ever when Graham Bell first introduced it .
However , ever since the internet became prevalent , the telephone started to give way to social media sites .
There are many advantages for the users .
As an example , let 's look at Facebook and Twitter , two of the most popular social media sites .
Through Facebook , people are able to maintain relationships with their old acquaintances .
This can not be achieved through phone or mail because people 's phone numbers and addresses may change from time to time while , on Facebook , people can keep in contact with old friends just by using their names and photos as identifiers .
Facebook is a combination of message and chat , personal profiles , sharing multimedia , and other entertainments , such as social games , which allow users to communicate with faraway people .
social games , which allow users to communicate with faraway people .
Twitter , which has a more straightforward function than Facebook , is more beneficial used as a vehicle for sharing information .
Twitter only allows users to post updates limited to short sentences in order to spread words quickly .
Facebook offers a more comprehensive way to share , since multiple photos and videos can be uploaded , long notes can be published , and even documents and data can be shared on the site .
These advantages come in handy as most of these social media sites are accessible through mobile applications on our smartphones .
Despite the benefits offered by social media , there are also harmful side effects that people may not be aware of beforehand .
Research shows that people who are addicted to social media sites meet face-to-face with decreasing frequency .
As a consequence , their interpersonal skills are affected .
People can think while typing and prepare what they want to say but , in face-to-face communication , every word that comes out of their mouth and may not be well arranged paints a picture of their personality .
This skill requires practice and can not be learned completely through social media .
In one scenario , a family is having dinner together in a restaurant but everybody is busy with their own gadgets , posting pictures to Facebook , updating their status on Twitter , or even chatting with friends .
These social media sites serve a purpose to connect people in spite of geographical boundaries but it does n't mean that the people near them should be neglected as a consequence .
This is related to the interpersonal skills mentioned before , which can decrease qualitatively if we are more used to facing gadgets instead of human beings .
Another disadvantage that affects other people is that , by only showing curated parts of our lives , we build a " false image " to show to the public .
We tend to only share happy moments on social media .
Because of this , other people start to think that our lives are full of happiness with no problems at all .
Other people then are influenced by us and tend to do the same .
As a result , people think worse of themselves , which may lead to depression and mood disorders .
This also reduces our sympathy , which is a serious social problem that affects a lot of people .
is a serious social problem that affects a lot of people .
As explained above , modern and sophisticated technologies do not always bring advantages .
There are a lot of disadvantages that people may not be aware of .
It is up to each person 's discretion and understanding to decide which side they want to take .
In conclusion , we should never forget to think of and calculate the potential benefit and loss of every decision that we make .
Nowadays , technological advancements greatly improve the lives of many people .
Most countries have witnessed an emergence of social media sites such as Facebook and Twitter .
Many people think that social media sites benefit the communication between people while others argue that they have several negative impacts on society .
One of the advantages of social media sites is that they can connect us more closely than before .
In earlier decades , when social media sites were not yet fully developed , people connected with others who lived far away by using the phone , or even writing letters .
However , calling a person by phone and writing letters have a cost , and sending a letter to someone who lives far away , especially in small villages , takes a lot of time .
The appearance of social media sites caused those problems to be solved .
People connecting through social media sites communicate without spending money , and it only takes a few seconds for messages to be received .
The advantages of social media sites are that they save money and time , which is convenient for many people .
Moreover , this also provides an alternative way for people to contact those whom they had not seen in a very long time , such as their friends from primary school and secondary school .
As we graduate from a school , we will probably lose contact with some of our friends .
Some of them may change their phone numbers and addresses , and we will not be able to find them through the phone or mail .
If phone calls and letters are the only way we had to contact them , we would probably not be able to find them .
Facebook and Twitter can serve as an alternative route to make connections with our old friends .
Therefore , social media sites serves as a platform for making connections .
Everything that comes with benefits will have disadvantages as well .
Social media sites also bring negative impacts to people and the society .
The advancement of social media sites makes people so reliant on them that some prefer using these sites to contact each other rather than talking to each other face to face .
Many people argue that this is the most serious problem brought by social media .
The use of social media sites indirectly causes a reduction in face-to-face communication in real life , which will in turn cause the loss of interpersonal skills for many people .
As we all know , interpersonal skills are essential for us to communicate with each other and to present our views and ideas .
The loss of interpersonal skills results in the inability for people to present their ideas well .
As a result , they will gradually lose the ability to compete with each other in society .
In conclusion , social media sites have both positive and negative consequences for people and society .
As a part of this modern society , we should learn to distinguish between the good and bad impacts brought by technological advancement , and learn to avoid the cons and maximize the benefits of social media sites .
With the advancement of technology in recent years , the demand to keep in touch with people and the latest news has become tremendous .
Some famous examples are social media sites like Twitter and Facebook .
With more than a billion users from all over the world , social media sites have demonstrated clearly their success in playing an important part in our lives .
However , there are arguments that life with social media results in a reduction in face-to-face human contact , which in turn affects interpersonal skills .
Let 's examine the advantages and disadvantages of using social media in our daily lives and society .
First and foremost , all social media sites are free .
All users need are an internet connection and an email account , so that everyone can have a Facebook or Twitter ID to start their journey in social media life .
Second , it helps people to keep in touch with one another .
Finding old friends through Facebook , for example , is easier than asking around in real life .
Social media helps to lessen the hassle of geographical distance and brings people closer .
Third , social media sites keep us up-to-date on the latest news and updates from almost everywhere in the world , all only a click away on the refresh button .
Last but not least , social media sites also link people together by allowing us to create our own groups , pages , or sites to share our hobbies , interests , and studies in particular subjects .
Hence , it is undeniable that these sites play an important role in our global inter-connected world .
However , social media sites also have a negative impact on humans .
Undeniably , they become more addicting when we spend more time socialising and interacting virtually .
We spend the majority of our time on sites like Facebook and Twitter and it affects our daily work productivity and performance .
In the corporate world , employers often block social media networks to prevent employees from spending their office time on their personal leisure instead of concentrating on their work .
Using text-messaging language as an informal way of communicating on social media networks also produces a bad impact for us in the long term .
The more time we spend on these sites , the less time we spend on face-to-face interaction with one another .
Hence it lessens valuable interaction between humans and the time we spend away from the computer screen or mobile phone .
In addition , there are also some false reports on social media sites , and false identities are used to insult or harass people , like the case of Heather Chua that occurred recently on Facebook .
These malicious comments often go viral which creates a strong negative effect on the person in real life , which might lead to an unwilling attitude on the part of the victim to interact with others in real life .
In conclusion , everything has a two-sided effect , and depends on how we exploit it .
With the current boom in technology , it is good for people to become more technology-savvy and to want to spend more time interacting with each other through social media sites ; however , it does not mean that we should neglect face-to-face human interactions , which play an even more important role in our lives .
As more and more social websites such as Twitter , Facebook and Weibo which have become ubiquitous , seamless , and imperative in our lives , people may worry about the young generation having problems in face-to-face communication skills .
However , I believe that the benefits brought by these online chatting rooms tremendously outweigh their liabilities .
Social media enables us to explore the world far away without paying for expensive airplane tickets and spending a one-week holiday .
The convenience is beyond description .
With a small smart phone or a computer at school , at work , or at home , we can easily make friends worldwide with a ' click ' and get to know about their life through having conversations with them and reading their blogs , photos , and statuses .
Compared to face-to-face interaction , online conversation makes it easier for strangers to talk to each other .
Since some information has already been revealed on a person 's home page , it is also easier to find some common topics to talk about .
Moreover , people usually like to boldly share their real feelings online with their masks having been removed in reality .
This has been indicated in a report done by Boston University in 2012 : 80 % of information posted online is true , while a person may lie 3 out of 10 times in real life .
This shows that a Facebook friend may know more about you than your close friend who does not have a Facebook account .
That is because we are lying about who we are in reality , while we have no reason to do that in the online virtual world .
Although sometimes the genuine sharing of information may be inappropriate or even harmful , such as the prevalent use of vulgarity and harsh comments , we can minimize those behaviors through strict regulations of content online .
Another advantage of social media is in aiding the spread of democracy .
People around the world could easily share their thoughts about their governments .
That eliminates the disadvantage of incomplete information for some remote rural regions , where people are less aware of what is actually happening around them .
One example is the 2012 riots that happened in Egypt and Zambia .
The idea of striving for democracy was passed from Egyptians to people in Zambia quickly , through the use of social media .
However , the government controls most of the media .
These social media may be tools of their campaign and of their manipulation of the thoughts of the public .
For example , in the 2012 general election in Singapore , Dr. Tan Chee Keong made use of Facebook to spread his campaign videos to the public .
Although , because of this , social media is still a much fairer and more transparent online platform for the public to share ideas compared to other traditional media .
Intensive use of social media does reduce the time people spend in face-to-face communication .
It is a common sight in a food court or restaurant for a group of people to be sitting together around a table , with each of them having a cell phone in their hands .
They are too busy with their way-too-many virtual friends , and some of them neglect the feelings of their real-life friends .
In this case , I have to say that to err is human .
What we can do is to educate the public about the importance of the friends sitting beside them , and teach them to manage their time well .
In conclusion , the use of social media has more advantages than disadvantages in our daily lives .
What we can do is to cautiously manage the time we spend online and manage the words we use online .
With the regulation of the government and relevant authorities , the virtual world would be a better world .
The role of social media sites in connecting people around the world is undeniable .
Thank to social media , communication among people all over the world is possible and can be done with ease .
Apart from the ease of communication despite the distance , there are many other advantages , such as knowledge sharing and trading .
Nevertheless , along with those advantages come disadvantages , such as the reduction in face-to-face human contact ( which affects interpersonal skills ) , privacy issues , and fraud .
Twitter , Facebook , and Skype are some social media sites which enable us to keep in touch with our friends or family who are in other cities or countries .
Through those sites we are able to talk to them , to know what their activities are and who their friends are , etc . From the surface point of view , it is no doubt that these sites help us to have a better relationship with our relatives , despite of the distance .
The sharing of information can be done faster through social media , as well ; that is why nowadays , many news publishers make their own social media account . For example , Channel News Asia has a Twitter account , and updates its followers with headline news .
This shows how news and information can be shared easily through social media .
Furthermore , since many teenagers and young adults are fans of social media , this information can reach them easily without them needing to watch or listen to news reports .
Due to the popularity of social media , many people start to do their business via these sites .
More and more advertisements can be found on Facebook . Whether it is our friends or professional brands selling their products online , we are able to buy and contact the sellers through those sites , which can be considered to be an advantage for us , the buyers .
However , is it the same when we keep in touch with someone virtually , compared to when we meet them personally ?
I do think there is a difference in it , and I believe many of us will agree .
When we write or communicate virtually , we can hide our true feelings , and may not become ourselves , since we do not want the other party to judge us .
Other than that , sometimes the message of one party can not be delivered properly to the other one since the communication is done through written language , and thus the ' tone ' of the message between when it is sent and when it is received may be different .
Many people are very brave in telling people about their opinions online , but in real life , some of them can be very shy and not outspoken at all .
This will lead to a bad interpersonal skill as well as a problem of trust .
Nowadays , we can not really trust new people whom we know from social media since we will never know whether they are even ' real ' .
Some people fake their identities in media sites so that they can know more people , and some may even cheat others .
In addition , the privacy issue has become more popular nowadays , since some people do not realize that they may be sharing some information that they are not actually willing to share in the first place .
Therefore , while social media sites undoubtedly have benefits in our lives , we should consider their drawbacks and thus use them wisely so that we can gain more of their benefits and so it disadvantages us in the smallest way possible .
It is a common scene that almost everyone using public transportation is looking at a phone or wearing a pair of headphones in today 's society .
The same pictures can be found in many developed and developing countries .
Some say that it is a necessary step for human revolution .
Social media sites like Twitter and Facebook are popular among people , because they allow them to connect with others even from different countries .
It also brings many negative effects such as the loss of face-to-face communication skills , which are important in the work place .
This essay will discuss the advantages and disadvantages of using social media in our daily lives .
One of the significant advantages of using a popular social media site is that people can reach each other easily , even if they have been without contact for a long time .
In this fast-paced and competitive world , people may not otherwise be able to keep in touch with others .
With the help of social media sites , people are able to upload their new discoveries and funny scenes , and they can be updated with new information from their friends .
Personally , I am studying overseas , and a busy study life keeps me away from contact with my old friends .
Using a common social media site with my friends helps me know what are their statuses nowadays .
And I am able to easily find a common topic when I contact them .
Many Malaysians cross the sea to work here in Singapore .
Many of them are busy at work and separated from their children .
One of the managers in my work place has the same situation .
After my manager taught her mother how to use Facebook , she was able to upload video clips of her grandchild .
Therefore , my manager would not miss the moments of her daughter 's growth .
Social media sites are also a very useful tool for people to start a new friendship or relationship .
People with the same preferences get connected or become closer .
Knowing this information , it is easier for people to approach each other .
Students can exchange their experiences studying , even when they are in different countries .
People are able to share the culture or pretty photos online so that others can share the joy with them .
Thus I believe that social media sites are a useful tool to help people know each other better .
However , social media sites are a double-sided sword ; they also bring in some negative effects on our daily lives .
One of the disadvantages that concerns many people is that people lose interest in face-to-face communication .
Many people like to use language to create pretend identities , and lose confidence when they talk to each other .
Although not everyone is good at public relationships even without the existence of the social media sites , we can not deny that it does affect some people in their ability to use interpersonal skills .
In conclusion , there is always a shadow when there is light .
We should take the advantages of the creatures we create , and try to avoid the negative effects .
Social media sites are supposed to be a very useful and convenient tool to use and to bring people closer in this globalised world .
The use of social media has largely influenced our ways of communicating with one another .
Online friends become real life friends and real life friends communicate with one another online .
Social media has changed our ways of exchanging information and interpersonal relationships profoundly .
There are advantages and disadvantages to this change .
Social media has reshaped the way of communication .
In real life , we communicate with one another as equal participants .
We share ideas and stories and forge friendships based on mutual respect .
However , communication on social media is largely based on " broadcasting and listening " .
When we use Facebook and post pictures and statuses , we are actively " presenting " façades of our lives to others .
When we use Facebook and post pictures and statuses , we are actively " presenting " façades of our lives to others .
We tend to post pictures with the best looks , and statuses that are funny .
We broadcast these façades of us to others .
The images we choose to present are tentatively considered .
The audience is not some specific person , but everyone we might know , or even the entire world .
There is an element of seeking out attention rather than expressing one 's true opinion on social networks .
On the other hand , the viewers are not the listeners .
They are just scrolling down pages and pages of pictures and statuses until they see ones which they might think are funny .
It is not the broadcasters themselves they care about , but the content .
This type of communication does not help in forging interpersonal relationships .
In real life , establishing friendship requires well-rounded understanding of one another and caring for one another .
The latter requires face to face interaction where we can show our emotions to the other .
One can not truly understand a person by only stalking his/her Facebook page where he/she carefully chooses what to present .
One can not truly show their emotions to another by texting some = ) signs .
The broadcasting and viewing model is not good for forging relationships .
However , it is good for sharing information .
On social media , everyone is a broadcaster and a viewer .
With my social network account , I seldom read newspapers or go to news websites anymore , because I can easily read them from the statuses of my friends .
If I am interested in politics , I can just follow some political newspapers or public figures .
I get news for shopping , clothes , and cosmetics from my friends .
If some of my friends have horrible taste in clothing and he posts them often , I can simply block him .
Information gets circulated .
The most popular information gets circulated the most so I seldom miss it .
Social networks play a role in providing and also filtering information .
This saves a lot of time for me from reading newspapers and watching TV .
Personally I feel more at ease on social media .
From the above two points of view , I think social media could forge more interest-based friendships .
With the help of social media , I become real-life friends with those from online forums with whom I share the same interest .
I also discover some of my friends ' interests which I have in common , so that talking to one another is much more about life , study , friends , and so on .
The communication does not focus on how we feel , or say to each other , but on whatever is interesting , or the content .
In this case , interpersonal skills are not as important because our goal is not to impress somebody , but to get the information that we are both interested in .
In conclusion , I think social media has reshaped interpersonal relationships from a more human-based friendship that requires sharing and caring between friends to a more information-based friendship that requires a mutual interest .
There are advantages and disadvantages to this ; however , whether it is good or bad , we are still not sure .
It is just different .
Advantages and disadvantages of using social media in daily life
People that live in the modern world really can not live without social media sites like Twitter and Facebook .
Almost all students and young adults possess a Facebook or Twitter account .
It is true that social media makes people able to connect to one another more conveniently .
However , it seems that for some , sharing parts of their lives such as videos and photos on the social media sites becomes really necessary .
An extremely interesting and ironic phenomenon was discovered , where a group of friends met and sat around a table , but none of them were really chatting with one another .
Instead , all of them were more interested in posting pictures of this " cheerful " meeting on their social media sites .
Therefore , there is a need to discuss the advantages and disadvantages of social media .
Social media enables people from different parts of the world to communicate with one another .
In the past , people used to write letters and send post cards to keep in touch with ones who lived far away from them .
It can take a few days or weeks for those messages to be received .
Nowadays , what people need to do is to just type in front of the computer in their own rooms .
And people on the other side will only need a second to receive the message .
Distance and time are no longer the problems , which is convenient , especially when instant chat is needed .
However , when people become more and more addicted to this convenience and fail to communicate with people who are close to them , their face-to-face interpersonal skills are lost .
Social media provides people a way of talking and chatting which can never be considered as a way of communication .
When people chat on those media sites , there is no eye connection , no emotional delivery , and even the expressions are typed in by using some combinations of punctuation .
For more convenience , sentences are shortened to simply three or four words such as lol ( which means laugh intensively ) and " asap " ( which means as soon as possible ) .
People indeed go to great lengths to make their words as short as they can .
At the same time , once they are communicating with people to their face , expressing themselves appropriately becomes a really big problem .
Social media also provides people with a huge amount of information about people and things that interest them .
For example , on Twitter , it is exciting to follow people that you adore , like famous stars from movie and TV series , business men , and entrepreneurs .
It makes people feel extremely close to their admirers ' lives and works .
Updated news that people care about can be easily obtained at any time by refreshing your social media sites on your smart phones and laptops .
However , after one has registered at unreliable social media sites , all the information you have posted will be a weapon against you in the future .
Furthermore , not everyone on social media sites is honest .
The profile picture may not be the person who that user says he or she really is .
The reason might just be that he or she just wants to " decorate " his or her face .
But there is a possibility that the person on the other side is deceiving you in order to obtain information against you .
The lack of a pledge of authenticity risks people 's privacy and the information that is shared on social media sites .
To sum up , social media has advantages and disadvantages in people 's daily lives .
It shortens the distance between people from all over the world and makes instant communication possible .
And it becomes more convenient to obtain and update information by using social media .
On the contrary , social media makes people lose their ability to communicate effectively in their real lives and makes people risk exposing their privacy to those whose identity can not be verified on social media sites .
How does social media help change our lives ?
With the development of the technology , social media has become more and more significant in the world .
People can not stop using it every day to express their feelings and ideas , which helps their friends know their lives better .
However , it also raises the concerns about whether it brings us more benefits , or a disaster .
Although it helps to connect us with our friends wherever we are , it at the same time reduces the chances for us to talk to our friends face to face , which may affect our interpersonal skills .
Thus , whether there are more advantages or disadvantages becomes a tough question for every human being .
Many people say they will support social media since it really helps them to have a closer view about how their friends are doing in other parts of the world .
This is especially true for people who are overseas .
To them , social media is the only resource they can use to know everything that happens in their home country , as well as the way they can show their lives to those they love .
What 's more , these days social media plays an important role in spreading information .
Nowadays , people can just easily post information to their Facebook accounts and wait for responses from others who are from different parts of the world , which brings us a huge amount of convenience .
It is quite significant , especially for young teenagers who would rather go to these sites to see the news and know what happened in this world than read the newspaper every day .
However , there are also a great number of people who are against this technology .
They worry a lot about the bad effect on teenagers who are still developing .
They point out that social media reduces the chance for us to talk face to face with the people around us .
The more we care about Facebook , the less time we have to spend with our friends .
Nowadays , it is quite common to attend parties where people prefer looking at their phones and reading posts on Facebook if they feel bored .
It makes people worry that if teenagers continue using social media frequently , their ability to talk to people will decrease .
They feel it will become difficult for them to find any topics to discuss with other people .
Personally , I strongly agree that social media brings more disadvantages than advantages .
Although it is useful as a means of letting other people know we live a good life , it wastes a lot of time , as well .
Put another way , if we took the time we spent wandering those sites , we might instead finish a book or do other more meaningful things .
We should keep in mind that there are still ways for us to communicate with family or friends .
Everything will be bad if we do n't know how to use these tools wisely , whether or not it is really good .
As a result , it is important for people to know that we need to be cautious about the time we spend on social media .
As stated above , I strongly believe that if we can use social media wisely rather than abusing it , we will all live a better life .
The advantage and disadvantage of social media
Nowadays , as technology is becoming increasingly advanced , more and more social media sites are showing up in our daily life .
You can see people using Facebook and Twitter through their smart phones or iPads on buses or on trains .
Some may claim that the appearance of these modern media will reduce the chance for people to communicate face to face .
This essay will illustrate the pros and cons of using social media in modern society .
First of all , social media can make it more convenient for people to make friends and contact each other .
Years ago , when these modern products were not around , the way for people to communicate was restricted to making phone calls , sending emails , or writing letters .
Some will take a long time , and some are not efficient enough for people to get their response .
However , social media solves these problems well .
People can contact their friends on the internet and get their reply very fast .
The communication is also not limited to words .
People can express themselves through pictures or emotions .
People can also get to know their friends ' state and mood by looking at their posts online .
Moreover , people can be aware of what is going on in social situations , see comments online , and share their opinions on these websites .
These social media make people 's lives much more colorful and provide a lot of fun .
However , social media can do some harm to people 's lives .
It causes people to spend more time chatting on the internet rather than communicating face to face , such that their interpersonal skills will be badly affected .
Some people spend a lot of time in it and forget their real life .
Actually , I have seen that some people are very funny and interesting when I am chatting with them online .
However , they are quite boring when I talk to them in real life .
Teenagers are developing their interpersonal skills and social skills when they are growing up .
If they spend too much time on social media , it may cause some problems for their mental development .
They may feel uncomfortable when they communicate with people face to face .
Some may spend less and less time with their family and not know how to express themselves .
Moreover , incorrect information on the websites will affect teenagers and confuse them .
Some may even do something wrong .
In conclusion , the presence of social media sites is a double-edged sword .
It can make our life simpler .
People can promote their friendships and relationships through these social media .
On the other hand , it can also make people forget to communicate with their family and friends in real life , and negatively affect their interpersonal skills .
But overall , the advantages far outweigh the disadvantages .
So we need to make the best use of these social media sites , and make it a fun way of adding some excitement when life is boring .
And we need to try to overcome the shortcomings .
We should remember to send greetings to our friends and family frequently .
Nowadays , with the advancement of technology , it is easy to communicate wherever you are .
The appearance of social media sites truly connects people closely .
People can know their friends ' recent looks , and interesting things happening to those people , just by checking Facebook or other social media sites .
We can not deny that social media sites truly help old friends to stay in touch , and provide the chance to communicate even with people in a different country .
However , social media sites reduce face-to-face communication , which affects interpersonal skills .
There are two advantages and two disadvantages of using social media in people 's daily life .
First , social media sites can connect people with their friends and parents .
By typing words and showing pictures , people can express emotions that they are otherwise too shy to express .
For example , on mother 's day , people are shy to say " I love you " to their mothers , so instead , they can type it on their mother 's Facebook page .
Then their mothers will receive the message and feel happy .
On the other hand , when a teenager is studying in a foreign country , the internet is the only way that he can communicate with his or her parents and friends .
Therefore , social media is truly good for people .
Second , social media sites are not limited to connecting people with their close friends .
People can also use Twitter and Facebook to learn about celebrities such as Obama and Bill Gates ; they can also get first-hand study materials on them .
They can learn how these people succeed , and they can also have the chance to talk with them and know their thoughts , all by using social media .
With the help of social media , a homeless person , or someone who needs money to cure a disease , can get the help from the world quickly , because once one person knows the information , he or she will share it to their " friends area " , and many people will learn about it and continue to spread the information to a person who can provide help .
On the other hand , there are also problems with the popularity of social media .
First , when people rely on social media to communicate with their friends and parents , they will become accustomed to communicating by typing instead of talking .
People even come to prefer to talk to their friends and meet their friends online , and gradually reject face-to-face communication .
Therefore , social media truly limits interpersonal skills , such that people lose the chance and the ability to practice talking and build a relationship with their friends .
Second , without communication in real life , people lose the ability to see what is true and false .
There are many people in social media with beautiful images and good content in their pages ; however in real life , they may not have jobs and may live poorly .
Teenagers may believe these people and be cheated and lose money or even their safety .
Therefore , social media is not safe , which is bad for a teenager 's development .
All in all , the appearance of social media truly helps people in many areas .
However , there exist some disadvantages which will affect people to some degree .
Advantages and Disadvantages of Using Social Media in Our Daily life and Society .
Nowadays , with the development of technology and society , social media has become more popular and also important in our daily lives .
We communicate with others using social media — such as Twitter , Facebook and microblogs — more and more frequently .
There is no need for people to go out of their homes to interact with others ; they chat online , share pictures , and tell others funny stories or what they have done .
It seems that people build a good relationship with others using social media , but problems arise .
People do not know how to talk with others face to face , especially strangers .
Then , we need to talk about the advantages and disadvantages of using social media in our daily lives and in society .
As for the advantages , there are two aspects : it is more convenient to contact others , and it is easier to know about others .
One advantage is that it is more convenient to contact others using social media .
In the old days , if one wanted to share some important news with someone who lived far away , he needed to write letters , which wastes time .
The long distance and time required made spreading the messages very difficult at that time .
Therefore , people might not have had contact with the faraway friends and relatives unless there were something important .
However , people can now contact anyone who can use a computer , anywhere in the world , at any time , and there is no delay .
The other advantage is that it is easier to know about others using social media .
Without social media , it is difficult for people to gain information about a stranger .
They may collect information about that person by asking his friends , colleagues , or family members .
And the information collected may not be intact and true .
Today , however , with the help of social media , people can easily get the information they want just by searching online , and learn about what that person did every day and at what time .
As for the disadvantages of social media in our daily life , they include wasting time , causing illness related to sitting a long time in front of a computer , the quick spreading of rumors and fake news , and most importantly , the lost ability to talk confidently to others face to face .
It is weird that people sit around the table but all face their phones instead of talking with each other .
If there is a joke on their Facebook page , they may talk to others in this way : " Hi , look , how ridiculous this is " ; then they laugh together .
No matter whether it is a party , a dinner , or just simply a get-together , there are always some people bowing their heads and playing on their phones , even while their family and friends are in front of them .
In conclusion , there are both advantages and disadvantages of using social media in daily life .
People should enjoy the advantages of social media while being aware of the disadvantages , and trying their best to avoid the disadvantages happening to them and their friends and family .
Today 's world is considered to be the era of social media sites , like Facebook and Twitter , which are attractively connecting people around the world .
However , some people worry that social networks can affect interpersonal skills because they reduce face-to-face human contact .
The advantages and disadvantages of using such social media sites in society are elaborated on as follows .
Nobody can deny social media 's advantages in the benefit it provides in connecting people , regardless of nationality , race , culture , and language .
Social media is a trending topic and an excellent means of communication .
First , social media brings convenience to the world .
It has erased the boundaries of distance and time .
There are no longer any worries about the time it takes to deliver letters and packages .
Nowadays , thanks to the help of social media , with just one click , you can contact your family and friends wherever you want .
You can share photos , videos , and every meaningful experiences of your life .
More importantly , it is cheap and easy to use social media .
Second , the social media network opens the door of opportunity for people , due to its great benefit in connecting them .
Many recent graduates can find jobs , thanks to Facebook and Twitter .
Young people can widen their relationships , meet new friends , and learn wonderful things in many parts of the world .
In the business area , social media is a good tool to develop and advertise products and services .
On the other hand , social media also has disadvantages that have had worrisome effects on society and have made it a controversial phenomenon .
More and more young people spend most of their time in the social media world and reduce face-to-face human contact , which can affect interpersonal skills and relationships in real life .
First and foremost , we should realize that the social media world is not trustworthy and real .
People can invent the personality and characteristics they want .
They can become anyone .
Although social media does create relationships , relationships and friendships are only firm and real if people have gone through experiences and communication in face-to-face interactions .
There is a story of a girl who lived in the social media world every night for eight years .
In a chat room , she developed a close relationship with eight people .
She talked with them every night , trusted them and shared her life with them .
Then , one day , she discovered that all eight people were actually a single person who was chatting with her using eight different identities .
Furthermore , the convenience of social media is also its weakness .
A lot of people use identifying information on social media sites , which can lead to crimes and deception .
People can use their information to deceive family and friends and banks to do bad things such as blackmail , steal from ATMs , and so on .
Last but not least , social media affects human interpersonal skills when people increase the time they spend on social sites and reject chances to interact with people through normal daily activities .
Recent research has shown that the more time people spend on social media sites , the less ambitious they become .
As a result , if this unexpected trend continues , it will negatively affect the young generation .
To summarize , everything has its own pros and cons .
So do social media networks .
It not only is convenient and beneficial for connecting people and developing business , but it also can damage people 's relationships and interpersonal skills .
Social media is only beneficial as long as we know how to use it in a correct and suitable way ; to develop people 's potential to the fullest , use of social media sites must be combined with normal daily interaction .
